The course provides an overview of Estonian folk art and of consumer educationObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of the historical development of crafts and home economics, the nature of crafts, as well as consumer education; to develop understanding of the nature and evolution of  folk textile, emphasising  individual parts of national costume  and the tradition of wearing it.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course students 1.	will  have an overview of the concept of folk art, national costumes of Estonian parishes and their development trends on the background of the history of costume and fundamentals of ornament;  2.	can  comprise a summary of a set of Estonian national costume based on literature and museum exhibits;  3.	will know the techniques of costume design and can prepare as well as analyse  methodological material for crafts lessons of second and third school stages;  4.	will analyse their consumer behaviour and the possibilities of applying acquired knowledge to practice.
